          "title": "Data Engineer (m/w/d)",
          "description": "<p><strong>START DATE</strong></p>\n<p>Immediately</p>\n<p>The position is available in Berlin, Leipzig, Cologne, Frankfurt am Main, Stuttgart or Munich!</p>\n<p><strong>YOUR TASKS</strong></p>\n<p>Your tasks as <strong>Data Engineer</strong> at <strong>[at]</strong> are diverse! You can find a small overview here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Design, develop, test, debug, automate, document and maintain data pipelines</li>\n<li>Select the technologies for implementing Data Analytics Use Cases</li>\n<li>Develop data pipelines based on cluster architectures</li>\n<li>Visualise data for different purposes</li>\n<li>Assess the quality of the data and carry out data cleansing if necessary</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>YOUR PROFILE</strong></p>\n<p>As <strong>Data Engineer</strong> at <strong>[at]</strong> you should bring the following with you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Successfully completed studies in computer science, computer science, data science or a comparable qualification</li>\n<li>At least 2 years of professional experience as software engineer, software developer, data engineer or similar professional field</li>\n<li>Very good knowledge of the programming languages Python, Java or Scala</li>\n<li>Knowledge of cloud technologies e.g. Azure or AWS</li>\n<li>Knowledge and experience in handling Hadoop ecosystems</li>\n<li>Willingness to travel as part of a consulting activity</li>\n<li>Ideally fluent German and English</li>\n</ul>\n",
